   <h1> Ingredients:</h1>
   <ul>
<li>1 lb (450g) ground beef</li>
<li>1 onion, diced</li>
<li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
<li>1 bell pepper, diced (optional)</li>
<li>1 tablespoon chili powder</li>
<li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon paprika</li>
<li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
<li>1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed</li>
<li>1 cup cooked rice</li>
<li>1 cup shredded cheese (such as cheddar or Monterey Jack)</li>
<li>4 large flour tortillas</li>
<li>Optional toppings: diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce, diced avocado, sour cream, salsa, chopped cilantro</li>
</ul>
<h1>Instructions:</h1>
 <h2>Cook the Meat:  </h2>
 <ul>
    <li>In a large skillet, cook the ground beef/meat over medium heat until browned and cooked through, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks. Drain any excess grease from the skillet.</li>
 </ul>

<h2>Add Aromatics:</h2>
<ul><li>Add the diced onion, minced garlic, and diced bell pepper (if using) to the skillet with the cooked beef. Cook for a few minutes until the vegetables are softened.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Season:</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Stir in the chili powder, ground cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook for another minute or until the spices are fragrant.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Add Beans and Rice: </h2>
<ul><li> Add the drained and rinsed black beans and cooked rice to the skillet with the beef mixture. Stir to combine and cook for a few more minutes until heated through.</li></ul>
<h2>Assemble Burritos: </h2>
<ul><li> Lay out the flour tortillas on a clean surface. Spoon some of the beef and bean mixture onto each tortilla, then sprinkle with shredded cheese. Add any optional toppings as desired.</li></ul>
<h2>Roll Burritos:</h2>
<ul><li> Fold the sides of each tortilla over the filling, then roll it up tightly from the bottom to enclose the filling.</li></ul>
<h2>Serve:</h2>
<ul><li>Serve the burritos immediately, or you can wrap them individually in aluminum foil and place them in a preheated oven (at 350°F or 180°C) for a few minutes to warm through before serving.</li></ul>
<h2>Enjoy:</h2>
<ul><li>Serve the burritos with additional toppings such as diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce, diced avocado, sour cream, salsa, and chopped cilantro. Enjoy your homemade beef burritos!</li></ul>

